<html
  xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
  xmlns:tal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/tal"
  xmlns:metal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/metal"
  xmlns:i18n="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/i18n"
  xml:lang="en"
  lang="en"
  dir="ltr"
  metal:use-macro="context/@@main_template/master"
  i18n:domain="malone">

  <body>
    <metal:leftportlets fill-slot="portlets_one">
      <div tal:replace="structure context/bug/@@+portlet-questions" />
    </metal:leftportlets>

    <metal:rightportlets fill-slot="portlets_two">
      <div tal:replace="structure context/@@+portlet-search" />
    </metal:rightportlets>

    <metal:main fill-slot="main">
      <div>
        <img alt="" src="/@@/bug" />
        <a tal:attributes="href context/bug/fmt:url"
        >Bug #<tal:bug replace="context/bug/id">3252543</tal:bug></a>:
        <tal:title replace="context/bug/title">Foo doesn't work</tal:title>
      </div>

      <h1>Convert this question back to a bug</h1>

      <metal:form use-macro="context/@@launchpad_form/form">
        <div metal:fill-slot="extra_info">
          <p tal:condition="not: view/has_question">
            The bug was not converted to a question. There is nothing
            to change.
          </p>

          <p>
            Reactivate this bug report by removing the question created
            from the bug. The bug's status, importance, etc.. can then
            be edited. The bug's status will not be updated for any project
            that it affects. A bug contact must update the appropriate
            status after the question is removed. The question will still
            exist--its status can be updated separately from this bug.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="actions" metal:fill-slot="buttons">
          <input tal:repeat="action view/actions"
            tal:replace="structure action/render"
            tal:condition="view/has_question" />
        </div>
      </metal:form>
    </metal:main>

    <metal:help fill-slot="help">
      <p>
        Choose 'Convert Back to Bug' to restore the bug report. The
        bug's status, importance, etc... in all locations that it affects
        can be edited again. A comment may be provided to explain that the
        bug reported is reactivated. After the question is removed, the
        bug's status should be updated for the affected project.
      </p>
      <p>
        The question is a separate entity from the bug. Its status will
        not be changed.
      </p>
    </metal:help>
  </body>
</html>
